@page "/docs/changelog"
@namespace Lumeo.Docs.Pages.Docs

<PageTitle>Changelog — Lumeo</PageTitle>

<Container MaxWidth="3xl" Padding="0" Center="false">
<Stack Gap="10">

    <Stack Gap="4">
        <Heading Level="1" Size="3xl">Changelog</Heading>
        <Lumeo.Text Size="base" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
            All notable changes to Lumeo are documented here. Each release groups changes into Added, Improved, and Fixed categories.
        </Lumeo.Text>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v2.0.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v2.0.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">April 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Lumeo.Text Size="base" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
            Lumeo 2.0 is a mega-release: AI chat primitives, motion primitives, dashboard tiles, Bento layout, Splitter, PickList, BottomNav, and 8 copy-paste block templates — plus the breaking removal of the v1.6 deprecation aliases. 130+ components total.
        </Lumeo.Text>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added — AI primitives</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">PromptInput</code> — auto-growing textarea with send button, leading/trailing slots, Shift+Enter newline</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">StreamingText</code> — token-by-token fade-in for SignalR-streamed LLM output</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">AgentMessageList</code> + <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">AgentMessage</code> — chat transcript with sticky auto-scroll, User/Assistant/System/Tool roles</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">ToolCallCard</code> — collapsible tool-invocation card with status, duration, input/output</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">ReasoningDisplay</code> — collapsible chain-of-thought panel with streaming pulse</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added — Motion primitives</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Marquee</code> — infinite-scroll track (Left/Right/Vertical, pause-on-hover)</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">NumberTicker</code> — RAF-driven count-up animation</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">TextReveal</code> — word-by-word scroll-triggered reveal</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">BlurFade</code> — blur + fade-in on IntersectionObserver</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">BorderBeam</code> — rotating conic-gradient border beam (pure CSS)</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">ShimmerButton</code> — button with shimmer sweep, reuses Button variant/size</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Sparkles</code> — animated sparkle overlay with stable seeded positions</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added — Dashboard tiles + Bento</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Bento</code> + <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">BentoTile</code> — container-query-aware grid with span/row-span</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">KpiCard</code> — KPI tile with value, delta pill, optional icon + spark slot</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">SparkCard</code> — compact tile with inline SVG sparkline</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Delta</code> — standalone +/- pill with configurable "good direction"</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added — Navigation + Forms</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">BottomNav</code> — mobile tab bar with safe-area-inset, optional center FAB, pill variant</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Splitter</code> + <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">SplitterPane</code> + <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">SplitterDivider</code> — multi-pane resizable layouts (horizontal / vertical / nested)</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">PickList&lt;T&gt;</code> — dual-list picker with search, generic ItemTemplate</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added — Block templates (copy-paste)</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">/blocks/sign-in</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">/sign-up</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">/reset-password</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">/otp-verify</code></li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">/blocks/pricing</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">/hero</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">/dashboard-block</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">/settings-page</code></li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Breaking changes</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>Removed <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">[Obsolete]</code> <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Icon</code> / <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Label</code> <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">RenderFragment</code> aliases from Alert, Badge, EmptyState, Rating, Result, Segmented, SidebarMenuButton, StepsItem, TabsTrigger, TimelineItem. Migration: rename <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;Icon&gt;…&lt;/Icon&gt;</code> → <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;IconContent&gt;…&lt;/IconContent&gt;</code> and <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;Label&gt;…&lt;/Label&gt;</code> → <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;LabelContent&gt;…&lt;/LabelContent&gt;</code>. These aliases were deprecated in v1.6.0.</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Interop additions</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">motion.*</code> JS module — RAF count-up, IntersectionObserver helpers for reveal/fade</li>
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">ai.*</code> JS module — textarea autosize, sticky scroll MutationObserver</li>
                <li>Pointer-capture helpers on <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">IComponentInteropService</code> for Splitter drag</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.6.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.6.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">April 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">IconContent</code> / <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">LabelContent</code> slots on Alert, Badge, EmptyState, Rating, Result, Segmented, SidebarMenuButton, StepsItem, TabsTrigger, TimelineItem — replace the previous <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Icon</code> / <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Label</code> slots that collided with the <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;Icon&gt;</code> and <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;Label&gt;</code> components</li>
                <li>Design philosophy section in Introduction docs explaining the unprefixed naming choice and the <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;Name&gt;Content</code> convention</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Deprecated</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>Old <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Icon</code> / <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Label</code> slot parameters remain as <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">[Obsolete]</code> aliases — existing code compiles with a warning; aliases are removed in 2.0</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.5.1 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.5.1</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">April 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;Icon&gt;</code> component — Lumeo-native wrapper around Blazicons with <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Name</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Svg</code>, and <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Size</code> (Xs, Sm, Md, Lg, Xl) parameters</li>
                <li>Icon finder docs page — search + library switcher across Lucide, Bootstrap, Heroicons, Feather, Octicons, Material, Fluent; reflection-based catalog covering all ~1,700 Lucide icons</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.5.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.5.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">April 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>Service interfaces — <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">IToastService</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">IOverlayService</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">IThemeService</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">IKeyboardShortcutService</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">IComponentInteropService</code> — for mockability in consumer tests</li>
                <li>DataGrid sticky header across scrolling viewport</li>
                <li>DatePicker support for <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">DateTime</code> binding alongside <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">DateOnly</code></li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Improved</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>DialogFooter button spacing, alignment, and responsive stacking polished</li>
                <li>DataGrid DX: cleaner row API, simplified column definitions, better defaults</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.4.1 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.4.1</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">April 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Fixed</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>Stacked bar chart: outer corners stayed sharp when theme had rounded corners — now uses per-segment <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">borderRadius</code> arrays so the theme's radius actually applies</li>
                <li>Dialog zoom-in animation transform leaked with <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">fill-mode: both</code> — keyframe end state switched to <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">transform: none</code></li>
                <li>DataGrid column race where the grid rendered empty until the first interaction — fixed with <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">InvokeAsync(StateHasChanged)</code> in <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">AddColumnDef</code></li>
                <li>Charts not repainting on theme change — JS dispatches <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">lumeo:theme-changed</code>; ECharts interop listens and rerenders</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.4.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.4.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">April 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>Rounded outer corners on stacked bar charts (top segment top-rounded, bottom segment bottom-rounded)</li>
                <li>Charts now rerender automatically on theme change — no page refresh needed</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.3.1 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.3.1</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">April 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Fixed</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>nupkg leaked <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">package.json</code> / <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">package-lock.json</code> and caused <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">NETSDK1152</code> publish conflicts in consumer apps — moved npm build to repo root and excluded <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Styles/</code> from the package</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.3.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.3.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">April 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>Pre-compiled <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">lumeo-utilities.css</code> ships in the package — zero-config Tailwind for consumers; no local Tailwind build required</li>
                <li>Consumers who want Tailwind in their own markup can keep their own v4 build and drop <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">lumeo-utilities.css</code> — their build picks up every utility Lumeo needs</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.2.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.2.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">April 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>Built-in EN/DE localization via <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">ILumeoLocalizer</code> — driven by <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture</code> with exact → neutral → English fallback</li>
                <li>Override or extend locales during <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">AddLumeo(opts =&gt; opts.Add(...))</code></li>
                <li>DataGrid, Pagination, DatePicker, and other component default strings now translatable</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Fixed</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>Stacked bar chart rendering on dark theme</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.1.2 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.1.2</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">March 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Fixed</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>PasswordInput browser-autofill yellow highlight bled past the input's rounded corners — now clipped to the input's radius</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.1.1 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.1.1</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">March 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Fixed</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>DataGrid pagination test assertion updated to match the new footer wording</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v1.1.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v1.1.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">March 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li>ColorPicker SV + Hue picker surface (replaces the earlier swatch-only design)</li>
                <li>Blocks polish pass — cleaner layouts across Authentication, Analytics, Calendar, Chat, Dashboard, E-Commerce, FileManager, Kanban, Settings, TaskTracker and more</li>
